value.value: The anatomical cluster that includes the labrum, hypopharynx and labium.
The carina that is located on the face, parallels the inner orbit and is paired.
The intersegmentalia that is located on the mesopectus-pronotum intersegmental membrane and corresponds to the site of origin of the anterior thoracic spiracle occlusor muscle.
The ridge that seperates the prescutum from scutum.
The sulcus that sets off the prescutum from the scutum and corresponds to the prescutal ridge.
The area that is located on the alinotum and is limited by the antecostal suture and prescutal suture.
The sulcus that delimits anteriorly the speculum and corresponds to the anterior margin of the speculum.
The area that is located between the first metasomal spiracle and metapleural arm and delimited laterally by the metapleural carina.
The area that is located on the basisternum and is delimited by the sternacostal sulcus.
The patch that is enlarged, sclerotized, and located at the apex of one or more wing veins on the anterior margin of the wing.
The anatomical cluster that is apical to the telotarsus and composed of the empodium, auxilia, planta, pulvillum, unguis, unguitractor plate, auxiliar sclerite and manubrium.
The anatomical space that is the transition from the ductus ejaculatorius to the endophallus and therefore the transition from the internal to the external male genitalia.
The area on the sclerite that is raised.
The discrimen that is located in the prothorax and corresponds to the prodiscrimenal lamella.
The discrimenal lamella that is located in the prothorax.
The anatomical cluster that is composed of the profurcal arms.
The sternal apophysis that is paired, arises from the furcasternum of the prothorax and continuous with the prodiscrimenal lamella.
The furcal pit that is located in the prothorax.
The laterocervical muscle that arises medially from the anterior surface of the dorsal profurcal lamella.
The process that is located on an edge.
The depression that is dorsomedian and is located on the pronotum.
The area of the pronotum that is subhorizontal and located posteriorly of the pronotal neck.
The setiferous patch that corresponds with the transverse sulcus of the pronotum.
The evagination that extends along the anterior margin of the pronotum and overlaps the head-propectus articulation.
The area that is located dorsally on the posterior margin of the pronotum and overlaps the anterior thoracic spiracle.
The area of the pronotum that is delimited posterodorsally by an edge and that accommodates the posterior surface of the head.
The area of the pronotum that is median, raised and limited laterally by sharp edges.
The projection that is part of the pronotum.
The corner that is located anterolaterally on the horizontal part of the collar.
The area that is located on the pronotum and that is vertical.
The sulcus that extends along the dorsal margin of the pronotum and delimits the dorsal pronotal area.
The verricule that is located on the anterosubmedial pronotum.
The laterocervical muscle that arises medially from the pronotum and insert on the cervical apodeme.
The mesobasalar muscle that originates from the posterolateral part of the pronotum and inserts on the mesobasalare.
The anterior thoracic spiracle occlusor muscle that arises from the pronotum.
The postoccipital muscle that arises from the pronotum and inserts on the postocciput.
The procoxal muscle that arises from the pronotum and inserts on the posterolateral margin of the procoxa.
The profurcal muscle that arises along the ventral margin of the pronotum, and inserts laterally on the profurca.
The prophragmal muscle that originates medially from the pronotum and inserts submedially on the prophragma.
The propleural muscle that arises medially from the pronotum and inserts on the posterodorsal margin of the propleuron.
The notum that is located in the prothorax.
The anatomical cluster that is composed of the prosternum and the propleuron.
The phragma that extends along the anterior margin of the mesonotum.
The apodeme that is located on the posterodorsal corner of the lateral propleural area and corresponds to the site of muscle attachment.
The sulcus that extends along the dorsal margin of the propleuron.
The epicoxal sulcus that sets of the epicoxal lobe from the ventral part of the ventral propleural area.
The postoccipital muscle that arises from the propleuron and inserts on the postocciput.
The procoxal muscle that arises from along the posterodorsal margin of the propleuron and inserts on the procoxa.
The protrochanteral muscle that arises from the propleuron and inserts on the protrochanteral apodeme.
